## Architecture Discipline

- Never mix backend, frontend, and data responsibilities.
- Always enforce separation of concerns.
- Keep systems modular and composable.

## Contract-First Principle

- API contracts must be defined before implementation.
- Frontend must never guess backend structure.
- Backend must never adapt to frontend assumptions ad hoc.

## PR Lifecycle Enforcement (MANDATORY)

- Every change must run full lifecycle: Idea -> Plan -> Contract -> Implementation -> Test -> Security -> Docs -> Audit -> Merge.
- **Merge sequencing:** merge **open** PRs targeting `main` (when CI is green) **before** starting unrelated new PR work, unless the user directs otherwise — see `PR-WORKFLOW.mdc`.
- **`meta` / formal OS sign-off:** automatic **ALLOW** by default; no blocking wait for `meta` unless the user explicitly escalates — see `PR-WORKFLOW.mdc`.
- No direct push to `main`.
- No feature without PR.
- No PR without tests.
- No merge without security check (may be automated / lightweight per workflow).
- No architecture change without `orch`.

## Branch Model

- `main` -> production
- `feature/*` -> new features
- `fix/*` -> bug fixes
- `research/*` -> data and PDF extraction work
- `audit/*` -> structural analysis and refactor planning
- `hotfix/*` -> urgent production fixes
- `test/*` -> validation-fix branches
- `release/*` or `release` -> release readiness

## Agent Responsibility Enforcement

- `meta`: governance and execution permission — **default automatic ALLOW**; blocking arbitration only when the user explicitly escalates
- `heal`: self-healing proposal generation only
- `orch`: planning, decomposition, delegation, PR lifecycle control only
- `backend-implementation-agent`: API and backend business logic only
- `frontend-implementation-agent`: UI and rendering logic only
- `research-agent`: extraction, normalization, data structuring only
- `test-agent-fast-ci` and `test-agent-strict-reviewer`: validation only
- `security-code-review-agent`: risk analysis only
- `code-audit-agent`: structural audit only
- `documentation-agent`: documentation only

## Delegation unavailable

If **Task/subagent delegation fails** (e.g. API usage limit, unavailable runner), the **parent agent** follows **`.cursor/rules/SUBAGENT-DELEGATION-FALLBACK.mdc`**: inlined orchestration checklist, explicit git hygiene verification, honest gate status — until delegation works again or the work unit closes.

## No Cross-Agent Violations

- Agents must not perform tasks outside their domain.
- No agent may redesign system architecture except `orch`.
- `meta` may block or guard execution **only when explicitly escalated by the user** but may not implement code.
- `heal` may generate proposal PRs but may not directly patch production code.

## Gate Failure Recovery Paths

- Test fail -> back to implementation.
- Security fail -> back to implementation.
- Audit critical fail -> refactor cycle.

## Commit Discipline

- Commits must be atomic.
- Preferred prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`.
- GitHub PR number is **mandatory in the commit subject line (first line)**: suffix **`(#NNN)`** (same convention as historical `9f638f5`: `fix: stabilize runtime contracts (#2)`). Draft PR early if needed; squash title must comply.

## Code Quality Standards

- Prefer clarity over cleverness.
- Avoid unnecessary abstraction.
- Keep functions focused and testable.

## Async Backend Rule

- FastAPI must use async-first design.
- No blocking I/O in backend layer.

## Frontend Rules

- React remains component-driven.
- three.js stays isolated from UI logic.
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders.

## Data Safety Rule

- All external input is untrusted and must be validated.

## Documentation Requirement

- Major features must be documented.
- API changes must be reflected in docs.

## Memory Layer Requirement

- Agents must read relevant files under `memory/` before significant actions.
- Agents must update `memory/` after critical decisions, bugs, or structural findings.
- Critical decision entries must include timestamps.
- Outdated entries must be marked `Status: deprecated`.

## Security Baseline

- No unsafe input handling.
- No direct exposure of internal errors.
- Validate all external data sources.
